HEADWORD: Epiphonema
<hw>Ep`i*pho*ne"ma</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr.
Gr. <grk>'epifw`nhma</grk>, fr. <grk>'epifwnei^n</grk> to mention;
<grk>'epi`</grk> + <grk>fwnei^n</grk> to speak.]</ety>
<fld>(Rhet.)</fld> <def>An exclamatory sentence, or striking reflection,
which sums up or concludes a discourse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

